[{"id":"VH934134","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a square sheet of cardboard. The square is divided horizontally into three sections, such that the vertical length of the top and bottom sections is x. The vertical length of the middle section is significantly greater than the other two sections. The square is also divided vertically into four sections. From left to right, the first and third sections each have horizontal length x. The second and fourth sections have the same horizontal length, and are longer than the first and third sections. Twelve rectangular pieces are created as a result of dividing the square horizontally and vertically. In the top horizontal section, the second rectangular piece is shaded. In the middle horizontal section, all four rectangular pieces are shaded. In the bottom horizontal section, the second rectangular piece is shaded.\" height=\"350\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH934134.g02.png\" width=\"350\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figure above represents a square sheet of cardboard with side length 40 inches. The sheet is cut and pieces are discarded. When the cardboard is folded, it becomes a rectangular box with a lid. The pattern for the rectangular box with a lid is shaded in the figure. Four squares with side length <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x\"><math alttext=\"x\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and two rectangular regions are discarded from the cardboard. Which of the following statements is true? (The volume <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v\"><math alttext=\"v\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>V</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>of a rectangular box is given by <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"v equals, l w h\"><math alttext=\"v equals, l w h\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>l</mi><mi>w</mi><mi>h</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.)</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH934134_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">When <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 20\"><math alttext=\"x equals 20\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow></math></span></span> inches, the box has a minimum possible volume.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">When <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 20\"><math alttext=\"x equals 20\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> inches, the box has a maximum possible volume.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">When <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals, the fraction 20 over 3\"><math alttext=\"x equals, the fraction 20 over 3\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> inches, the box has a minimum possible volume.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">When <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals, the fraction 20 over 3\"><math alttext=\"x equals, the fraction 20 over 3\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>20</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> inches, the box has a maximum possible volume.</p>"],"answer":3}]